<Window x:Class="Help_NewLeague"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:FntasyFootballPro"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Height="340" Width="400" WindowStyle="none" ResizeMode="NoResize" ShowInTaskbar="False" Topmost="True">
    <Border Style="{StaticResource HelpBD}" BorderThickness="1">
        <StackPanel Style="{StaticResource HelpSP}" Height="330" Width="390" Orientation="Vertical" >
            <Label Style="{StaticResource HelpTT}" HorizontalAlignment="Center">Create New League Form</Label>
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpTB}" Width="370" Height="250" Margin="5,5,5,0" >
The New League form allows you to define a new league and contains<LineBreak/> two tabs: <Bold>Settings</Bold> and <Bold>Teams.</Bold><LineBreak/><LineBreak/>

<Bold>Settins:</Bold><LineBreak/>
On this tab you specify such information as the league and<LineBreak/> champoinship game name, starting year and structure of your league.<LineBreak/>  
The structure of your league will specify the number of teams, division,<LineBreak/> conferences, games in a season and number of playoff teams for your<LineBreak/> leage.  
Once you chose a league structure, you can then specify names for the conferences and divisions corresponding to your choice.<LineBreak/>
<Span Foreground="Red"><Bold>Caution:</Bold></Span> Changing the league structure selection will wipe out <LineBreak/>conference\division names and any teams you create\select on the teams tab, so be sure to decide your league structure early.
<LineBreak/>
<LineBreak/>                
<Bold>Teams:</Bold><LineBreak/>
On this tab, you populate your league with teams.  <LineBreak/>There are two ways to populate your league with teams:  You can <LineBreak/>double-click an Empty Team Slot and manually create a team, or you <LineBreak/>can drag-and-drop a stock team to an Empty Team Slot.
Note that once <LineBreak/>you poplate an Empty Team Slot with a team, you can update it by <LineBreak/>double-clicking, and it is also possible to move a team from one slot to <LineBreak/>another via drag-and-drop.

            </TextBlock>
            <Button Name="hlp_nl_close" Style="{StaticResource appSubmitStyle}">Close</Button>
        </StackPanel>
    </Border>

</Window>

